title: Faster With Newbern and Cotten
subTitle: David Newbern and Mike Cotten use their knowledge and resources to transform cars and make them better, faster and stronger on a budget.

title: Kings of Crash
subTitle: Hard-hitting demolition derby drivers overcome numerous obstacles to compete in one of Utah's highest-paying events.

title: Salvage Hunters: Classic Cars
subTitle: A rare, half-built Land Rover Series-2a gives Drew the opportunity to be able to create his dream Safari 'Landie'. With some of the accessories no longer available, the artisans step in.

title: Wheeler Dealers
subTitle: Mike wants to splash the cash on a custom bus but Edd favours a more conservative campervan. Edd is an air-cooled expert so this strategy may pay dividends.

title: Bad Chad Customs
subTitle: In rural Canning, Nova Scotia, Chad Hiltz runs a modest auto body shop with a legendary reputation. A custom car artist and master builder, 'Bad Chad' and his tight-knit team can turn metal from the junkyards into award-winning cars.

title: Put Up or Shut Up
subTitle: At the Blair Bedford Dirt Drags in Pennsylvania, two top fuel bikes compete against each other. The focus there is on acceleration with nitromethane. The distance is only 150 metres so every second counts.

title: Put Up or Shut Up
subTitle: Two of America's top modified pulling tractors compete in the ultimate, heavy duty drag race. Randy Davis races against Keith Wayson in their giant, modified 6,000 horse power beasts.

title: Salvage Hunters: Classic Cars
subTitle: A classic Fiat 124 Spider race car offers the boys the chance to be able to fulfil their heritage racing dreams. However, it's a tight fit and Drew despises its green colour scheme.

title: Wheeler Dealers
subTitle: Mike hunts down the cheapest Audi TT Quattro he can find - which is at the end of a 300-mile journey down to Cornwall. Edd needs to fix the gearbox and make a profit for them.

title: Dirt Every Day
subTitle: Fred and Dave head to Idaho, with a huge task on their hands. They are attempting to modify a high-mileage regular cab Chevy into a supercharged truck on skis with a lot of horsepower.

title: Dirt Every Day
subTitle: In an epic 4x4 rescue mission, Fred and Dave head to Oregon to get hold of a junkyard truck to take out on the dunes. They are hoping to give the sad looking truck a new lease of life.

title: All Girls Garage
subTitle: The crew diagnoses and fixes some problems on a Dodge Avenger; they demonstrate how to know when motor mounts are bad, and how to easily fix a cracked bumper.

title: All Girls Garage
subTitle: The team brings in a stock supercharged CTS-V and converts it to twin turbos; they put an intake manifold where the supercharger was, and then put in a new exhaust that includes turbos.

title: Salvage Hunters: Classic Cars
subTitle: Drew and Paul rescue a classic: a Vauxhall Viva. The car was extensively modified in the 1960s but after years in storage, it's well past its best.

title: Wheeler Dealers
subTitle: Mike tracks down a Lincoln Continental, which set new style standards for luxury sedans in the 1960s. Tastes have changed and Edd hatches a refurb plan.

title: Car Kings
subTitle: Beau Boeckmann and the crew resurrect a Pantera hot-rodded by Carroll Shelby for a secret project. A famous client picks up his restored '68 Charger.

title: Street Customs
subTitle: Noel Lee, founder of Monster Cable, asks Ryan Friedlinghaus and company to transform his Bentley by adding a lift in order to get his Segway into the car's boot.
